
[1]sinecure

   SI'NECURE, n. [L. sine, without, and cura, cure, care.] An office which
   has revenue without employment; in church affairs, a benefice without
   cure of souls. [This is the original and proper sense of the word.]
   Sine die, [L. without day.] An adjournment sine die is and adjournment
   without fixing the time of resuming business. When a defendant is
   suffered to go sine die, he is dismissed the court.
